The paper deals with the verification of safety and liveness properties in the context of Petri nets, which are a standard model for distributed systems. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category, which deals with the use of logic and formal methods in computer science. Additionally, the paper involves the study of structural properties of Petri nets, which could fall under the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DS) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of Presburger arithmetic, which is a type of first-order arithmetic that can express certain properties of Petri nets, suggesting that the paper could belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category. Furthermore, the paper deals with the decidability of a problem, which could fall under the Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the study of reachability sets, which could fall under the Symbolic Computation (cs.SC) sub-category.
